</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB636D20969FFA32AD65063FA06FAF1" blockId="11.[151,1437,1087,1401]" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">
Comments: This endemic species is common in the archipelago. Undoubtedly, the species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D510969FFA32F5B5063FA15FADC" box="[1354,1436,1339,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Eriopis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAC00969FFA32F5B5063FA15FADC" box="[1354,1436,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="512">Eriopis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus, but it differs from the others by presenting insular gigantism and other morphological differences.
</paragraph>
